THE PDP state House of Assembly primary in Jigawa State was held at 12a.m and House of Representatives took place at 2p.m. The delegates converged at the 30 state assembly constituency headquarters for the House of Assembly primary, after which they moved to the headquarters of the 11 House of Representatives’ constituencies headquarters. The two primaries were done through consensus.   Elumelu, Abia Speaker win primaries     Delay trails primaries in Plateau     PDP suspends primary indefinitely in Imo   All the 30 state House Assembly and 11 House of Representatives were announced unopposed and affirmed by the delegates The state PDP Chairman, Babandi Ibrahim Gumel, while commenting on the exercise, expressed appreciation to the party’s leader in the state, Alhaji Sule Lamido, for his support and guidance. He lauded the delegates, the INEC officials, security and the mass media for their cooperation.